{
    "name": "Titan Centipede",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> temperate or warm forests or underground <br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or colony (3\u20136) <br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Poison (Ex)</b> Bite\u2014injury; <i>save </i>Fort DC 24; <i>frequency </i>1/round for 6 rounds; <i>effect </i>1d6 Dex; <i>cure </i>2 consecutive saves."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The largest of their kind, titan centipedes are thankfully also the rarest. They attack other living creatures fearlessly, and require constant sustenance to nourish their vast bulk. Humanoids are in most danger from titan centipedes when mounted rather than afoot\u2014a good-sized horse makes a much more satisfying meal to the centipede than a few bites of human. Titan centipedes are solitary by nature and because of the demands of their appetite, though when food is plentiful, multiple centipedes sometimes lurk in the same area."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>A writhing, seemingly endless segmented monstrosity crawls forth, its great mandibles clacking as it spies prey. </i>",
